   analytics},
Journal = {WILEY INTERDISCIPLINARY REVIEWS-DATA MINING AND KNOWLEDGE DISCOVERY},
Year = {2023},
Volume = {13},
Number = {1},
Month = {JAN},
Abstract = {The advent of technological developments is allowing to gather large
   amounts of data in several research fields. Learning analytics
   (LA)/educational data mining has access to big observational
   unstructured data captured from educational settings and relies mostly
   on unsupervised machine learning (ML) algorithms to make sense of such
   type of data. Generalized additive models for location, scale, and shape
   (GAMLSS) are a supervised statistical learning framework that allows
   modeling all the parameters of the distribution of the response variable
   with respect to the explanatory variables. This article overviews the
   power and flexibility of GAMLSS in relation to some ML techniques. Also,
   GAMLSS' capability to be tailored toward causality via causal
   regularization is briefly commented. This overview is illustrated via a
   data set from the field of LA. This article is categorized under:
   Application Areas > Education and Learning Algorithmic Development >
